name: Sheriff Octopus & Deputy Jellyfish
description:
Illustrated as one of the days of Inktober, this was part of a series of days where I drew anthropomorphic, aquatic western characters. The art was originally done in ink and colored pencil. Inktober was a month-long analog illustration extravaganza throughout October 2013. 

These are printed on acid free, Arches Velin Museum Rag, smooth, pure white, 250g, 8.5 x 11 sheets.

7 in. x 7 in.
